#lg B	kicu


@(B.112 = 112-133) The hero is a powerful force; may his storm leave no rain behind! The hero @wDN{Ninurta} is a powerful force. The hero @wDN{Pabilsaŋ} is a powerful force. The hero @wDN{Ninŋirsu} is a powerful force; may his storm leave no rain behind! My king is the pillager of cities for his father. O his valour! The hero @wDN{Ninurta} is the pillager of cities for his father. The hero @wDN{Pabilsaŋ} is the pillager of cities for his father. The hero @wDN{Ninŋirsu} is the pillager of cities for his father. O his valour! My king, …… the mountains, you ……. Hero @wDN{Ninurta}, before you the land swells (?) as if …….

@(B.134 = 134-164) My king, you covered the edge of the sea with rays of light. On that day from the gold (?) of @wGN{Ḫarali} you are @wDN{Ena-tum}. From the cornelian and lapis lazuli of the land of @wGN{Meluḫa} you are @wDN{Ena-tum}. From the @fsux{dušia} stone of the land of @wGN{Marḫaši} you are Enakam. From the silver of fifteen cities you are Enakam. From the copper and tin of @wGN{Magan} you are Enakam. From the bronze of …… you are Enakam (?). From the silver of @wGN{Dilmun} you are @wDN{Ena-tum}. From the @fsux{im-kalaga} clay of the mouth of the hills you are Enakam. From the gypsum of the shining hills you are Enakam.  @gap{10 lines missing or fragmentary} 

@(B.165 = 165-171) House of the rebel lands! Ah you! You! Ah me! Me! House of the rebel lands, when will your clay return to its @fsux{abzu}? House of the rebel lands, when will your reeds return to their reedbeds? House of the rebel lands, when will your beams return to their forests?

@(B.172 = 172-183) The enemy …… on the wall, and pays homage. My king, if only he knew your outstanding strength! Hero @wDN{Ninurta}, if only he knew your mighty awesomeness! If only he knew your devouring of men like a lion! If only he knew your …… like a dragon! If only he knew your …… kid and lamb like a lion!

